4cny1665703261952.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cny1665703261952.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cny1665703261952.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cny1665703261952\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the name and location of the Uniface system directory.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"cny1665703261952__topic_d145526e1_d145527e1_d145528e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cny1665703261952__p_d145529e1_d145530e1_d145531e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DirectoryPath</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"cny1665703261952__section_w3228ab1b5b3_w3229ab1b5_w3230ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"cny1665703261952__table_d17735e1_d17736e1_d17737e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceApsDir</var>/common/usys</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"otb1665703261079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/otb1665703261079.html\" title=\"The [paths] section of the initialization file specifies the locations of the local working directory, help files, images, and JavaScript files generated during compilation.\">[paths]</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cny1665703261952__section_drt_y5p_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d749038e110\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">If this cannot be resolved, the default is the current directory. Some Uniface files are\n            assumed to be in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">USYS</span> subdirectory, but can be moved to a\n            different location by adding an entry to <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span>. These files\n            include Uniface application forms.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526540\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526540\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USYS Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the name and location of the Uniface system directory. USYS = DirectoryPath Default value UnifaceApsDir /common/usys File section [paths] Description If this cannot be resolved, the default is the current directory. Some Uniface files are assumed to be in the USYS subdirectory, but can be moved to a different location by adding an entry to usys.asn . These files include Uniface application forms. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}